# Hand the classified delivery off to the ticketing service.
# The op's HTTP request body is the full envelope; the service
# reads `_txc.lmtp.*` + `_txc.ticket.*` to mint a row.
#
# The accept verdict was already written at scope 0 — Postfix gets
# 250 regardless of whether the downstream HTTP call succeeds.
# Failing here would log + emit metrics; it would NOT undo the
# accept (we already committed to handling the mail).
EXEC "op://TICKET_CREATE"
